data.title: Irish fans set for frenzy as iconic noughties DJ announces gigs 18 years after top hit
data.meta_description: THE iconic noughties group Cascada has announced two Irish gigs 18 years after their top hit.The German dance act was founded in 2004 by singer Natali
data.text:
THE iconic noughties group Cascada has announced two Irish gigs 18 years after their top hit.

The German dance act was founded in 2004 by singer Natalie, DJ Manian and DJ Yanou, making hit singles Everytime We Touch, What Hurts the Most, Evacuate the Dancefloor and Miracle.

They sold over 30 million albums worldwide, represented Germany at the Eurovision Song Contest in 2013 and was named as the third most successful German act of the 21st century.

The DJs released their legendary hit Everytime We Touch 18 years ago in 2005 in the United States and re-released it internationally in 2006.

The song peaked in the number one position in Ireland.

Cascada have recently announced their Irish gig at The Academy, Dublin.

They will be DJ-ing at the nightclub on Friday March 1, 2024, from 7pm.

Tickets for the highly anticipated event go on sale tomorrow at 9am on Ticketmaster.

Eventgoers must be over 18s and ID is required for entry.

Cascada is also set to join Basshunter, DARREN STYLES, Flip N Fill v Ultrabeat, Kelly Llorenna dn DJ Sash for the Clubland Arena Tour next year in Belfast.

The tour has been billed as: "Your chance to see the biggest artists performing their biggest tunes."

The event is taking place at the SSE Arena Belfast on Sunday May 5, hosted by Keyes and Finchy.

Tickets are priced from €53.40 to €62.59 and are on sale this Friday November 10 at 9.30am on SSEArenaBelfast.com.

Hitmaker Tate McRae also revealed she's heading to Dublin for two nights next year as part of her new tour - Think Later.

The tour comes in support of her new album, Think Later, which is due to debut on November 18, 2023.

It will take place across 53-dates throughout Europe, UK, North America, Australia, and New Zealand.

The tour will kick off with shows in Dublin’s 3Olympia Theatre on 17th and 18th April 2024.

TOP TATE

Think Later, set to be released on 8th December via RCA Records, is executive produced with hitmaker Ryan Tedder, and features songs steeped in pop appeal and infectious toplines.

Showcasing Tate’s boundless vocal talent and evolution as a songwriter, this new body of work explores the all-too-relatable feelings of falling in love and embracing the raw emotions that you experience as a result of leading with your intuition and heart.

Think Later features Tate’s latest single “greedy” which earned the star her first #1 on the Spotify Global chart and top 10 on the Billboard Global 200 chart hitting #3.

Tickets €51.40 including booking fees on sale Friday 10th November at 10AM.

People can only buy six tickets and one who exceeds the ticket limit may have any or all of their orders and tickets cancelled without notice by Ticketmaster at its discretion.

This includes orders associated with the same name, e-mail address, billing address, credit card number or other information.
